                "comment": "He struggles with ADD as well as dyslexia so sometimes its hard for him to understand questions or explain in different ways but he really loves teaching and helping students grow. He never talks badly of his students and is always excited to talk about them. I would know I live with the man. Remember he is also a person with his own hardships. SC",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "My son Chanda! He was the best professor out of all the unit in Phys 335! What you see in the lecture notes is what you get on the test! Nothing more, nothing less!  He has an accent so it is hard to understand him at first, but once you get used to it, he does a great job of explaining. Would recommend this professor to anyone!",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "When you look up the definition of an excellent professor Chanda's face should be right there. Through his exams and teaching styles you can tell that he is there to help you learn and not ruin your GPA. He's clear cut, genuine and wholeheartedly a chill guy! Having him teach my Physiology section gave me the confidence to continue this semester",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
